2500|$|In May 2001, the Committee on Non-Governmental Organizations of the United Nations heard {{arguments}} {{for and against}} Freedom House. Representatives of Cuba said that the organization is a U.S. foreign <b>policy</b> <b>instrument</b> linked to the CIA and [...] "submitted proof of the politically motivated, interventionist activities the NGO (Freedom House) carried out against their Government". They also claimed a lack of criticism of U.S. human rights violations in the annual reports. Cuba also stated that these violations are well documented by other reports, {{such as those of}} Human Rights Watch. Other countries such as China and Sudan also gave criticism. The Russian representative inquired [...] "why this organization, an NGO which defended human rights, was against the creation of the International Criminal Court." ...|$|E
